CV measurements may offer first insights into the ionic defect landscape of the devices. We performed these measurements at an ac frequency of 80 kHz using a fast sweep rate of 30 V/s in the reverse scan direction. Following the methodology of Fischer et al51. the devices were pre-biased for 60 s at 1 V, in order to minimize the influence of mobile ions present at the interfaces of the active layer. The results of the CV measurements (Supplementary Fig. 3a) were evaluated using the Mott–Schottky approach52,53:11/C2=2(Vbi−V)eϵ0ϵRNeff,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
