Advanced spectroscopic techniques such as IS and DLTS offer further insights into the defect landscape of the devices. In an IS experiment, the current response to an externally applied alternating voltage at a certain frequency ω is measured and considered as a capacitance signal by taking into account the imaginary part of the impedance Z57,58:3C=Im(1/Z)ω,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
